body: You can close this.  I got ACL 19.08 to compile and run with onnxruntime.
Hi Dan, I am facing some issues while doing the same. Would you be able to help me with that?
I could not get onnxruntime to compile using ACL 20.05.  I can post the list of changes I had to do to get onnxruntime to compile and run with ACL 19.08.  Are you interested in that?

Get onnxruntime v1.3.1:
‚Äã‚Äã

git clone --single-branch --recursive --branch v1.3.1 https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime

OR, if https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/VERSION_NUMBER is 1.3.1, then get latest:

git clone --single-branch --recursive --branch master https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime

I am using master from Jul 9th, 2020.

Get ArmComputeLibrary v19.08:
Currently, I can compile onnxruntime v1.3.1 with ACL v19.08.

https://github.com/ARM-software/ComputeLibrary/releases 

‚Äã‚Äã

Scroll down to v19.08 and click that.
Click on 'Source code (tar.gz)' to download.
/dump/dump201/dhunt/tar -xvf ComputeLibrary-19.08.tar.gz
‚Äã‚Äã


‚Äã‚Äã

‚Äã‚Äã

Be sure tools are installed
1) cmake

Install cmake-3.13 or higher from https://cmake.org/download/

Latest Release (3.17.3)
cmake-3.17.3-Linux-x86_64.tar.gz

Just download and unzip and add this to the path:
export PATH=/dump/dump201/dhunt/cmake-3.17.3/bin:$PATH

‚Äã‚Äã

2) protoc

 https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protobuf/releases

 

Scroll down to find

Protocol Buffers v3.11.3

protoc-3.11.3-linux-x86_64.zip
‚Äã‚Äã

Download and unzip the utility, 'protoc --version' shows it is 3.11.3.

dhunt@ubu-sw4:/dump/dump201/dhunt/onnxruntime$ /dump/dump201/dhunt/protoc_3.11.3/bin/protoc --version
libprotoc 3.11.3
‚Äã‚Äã

You will pass the path to the protoc bin in the cmake call shown below.

‚Äã‚Äã

Added to my bash environment in .bashrc:
‚Äã‚Äã

# For onnxruntime compile
export ACL_VER="19.08"
alias goonnx='cd /dump/dump201/dhunt/onnxruntime'
alias goacl="cd /dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-${ACL_VER}"
export PATH="/dump/dump201/dhunt/cmake-3.17.3/bin:$PATH"
export CPATH="/dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-${ACL_VER}/include:/dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-${ACL_VER}:$CPATH"
export LD_RUN_PATH="/dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-${ACL_VER}/build"
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH="/dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-${ACL_VER}/build"
‚Äã‚Äã

‚Äã‚Äã

Edit some files in ArmComputeLibrary
dhunt@ubu-sw4:/dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-19.08$ grep -n -r dhunt *
arm_compute/core/Helpers.inl:117:        ARM_COMPUTE_UNUSED(w, iterators...); // Added by dhunt to fix compile warning/error in onnxruntime v1.3.1
arm_compute/core/NEON/kernels/assembly/gemm_common.hpp:98:    virtual void set_quantized_bias(const int32_t *bias) { ARM_COMPUTE_UNUSED(bias); } // dhunt editted this line
‚Äã‚Äã

support/ToolchainSupport.h:74:    ARM_COMPUTE_UNUSED(pos); // dhunt added this line
support/ToolchainSupport.h:100:    ARM_COMPUTE_UNUSED(pos); // dhunt added this line
‚Äã‚Äã

Build ArmComputeLibrary
Use ubu-sw1, as that is where 'scons' is installed.

dhunt@ubu-sw1:/dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-19.08$ scons -j8 arch=arm64-v8a  Werror=1 debug=0 asserts=0 neon=1 opencl=1 examples=1 build=cross_compile  toolchain_prefix=/usr/local/linaro-aarch64-2018.08-gcc8.2/bin/aarch64-linux-gnu-
‚Äã‚Äã

‚Äã‚Äã

Configure the make environment for onnxruntime using cmake:
‚Äã‚Äã

Have this file up 1 directory:

dhunt@ubu-sw4:/dump/dump201/dhunt/onnxruntime$ cat ../tool.cmake
    SET(CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME Linux)
    SET(CMAKE_SYSTEM_VERSION 1)
    SET(CMAKE_C_COMPILER /usr/local/linaro-aarch64-2018.08-gcc8.2/bin/aarch64-linux-gnu-gcc)
    SET(CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER /usr/local/linaro-aarch64-2018.08-gcc8.2/bin/aarch64-linux-gnu-g++)
‚Äã‚Äã

Note: the linaro-gcc compiler might be installed elsewhere on the ubu-swX build machine that you are using.

In onnxruntime top directory, run this cmake command:

dhunt@ubu-sw4:/dump/dump201/dhunt/onnxruntime$ cmake -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=/dump/dump201/dhunt/tool.cmake -Donnxruntime_CROSS_COMPILING=ON -Donnxruntime_RUN_ONNX_TESTS=OFF -Donnxruntime_DEV_MODE=ON -DPYTHON_EXECUTABLE=/opt/amba/cv2_third/tv2/exe/python3 -Donnxruntime_USE_CUDA=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_NSYNC=OFF -Donnxruntime_CUDNN_HOME= -Donnxruntime_USE_JEMALLOC=OFF -Donnxruntime_ENABLE_PYTHON=OFF -Donnxruntime_BUILD_CSHARP=OFF -Donnxruntime_BUILD_SHARED_LIB=ON -Donnxruntime_USE_EIGEN_FOR_BLAS=ON -Donnxruntime_USE_OPENBLAS=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_DNNL=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_MKLML=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_OPENMP=ON -Donnxruntime_USE_TVM=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_LLVM=OFF -Donnxruntime_ENABLE_MICROSOFT_INTERNAL=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_BRAINSLICE=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_NUPHAR=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_EIGEN_THREADPOOL=OFF -Donnxruntime_BUILD_UNIT_TESTS=ON -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo -Dprotobuf_WITH_ZLIB=OFF -DONNX_CUSTOM_PROTOC_EXECUTABLE=/dump/dump201/dhunt/protoc_3.11.3/bin/protoc -DCMAKE_VERBOSE_MAKEFILE=ON -Donnxruntime_USE_ACL=ON -Donnxruntime_USE_ACL_1902=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_ACL_1905=OFF -Donnxruntime_USE_ACL_1908=ON cmake

‚Äã‚Äã

Make soft links to the ACL library .so files:
dhunt@ubu-sw4:/dump/dump201/dhunt/onnxruntime$ ln -s /dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-19.08/build/libarm_compute.so
dhunt@ubu-sw4:/dump/dump201/dhunt/onnxruntime$ ln -s /dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-19.08/build/libarm_compute_core.so

dhunt@ubu-sw4:/dump/dump201/dhunt/onnxruntime$ ln -s /dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLibrary-19.08/build/libarm_compute_graph.so

‚Äã‚Äã

Some of the tests look for the ACL library files here, at the top of the onnxruntime tree.

Some of the onnxruntime code finds the ACL .so files with -L /dump/dump201/dhunt/ComputeLbrary-19.08/build.  cmake creates files with the link commands that will look into the ACL tree.  And it gets that directory from LD_LIBRARY_PATH in the environment, which is set as shown above in the .bashrc file.

So, order matters.  bash environment is set, then cmake runs, then make.

‚Äã‚Äã

‚Äã‚Äã

Edit some files in onnxruntime tree
In onnxruntime, I changed these files:

onnxruntime/core/providers/acl/acl_execution_provider.cc

onnxruntime/core/providers/acl/acl_common.cc

onnxruntime/core/providers/acl/nn/conv.cc

In onnxruntime/core/providers/acl/acl_execution_provider.cc, pretend to use the return value from Register():

Status ret_val;
ret_val =
kernel_registry.Register(BuildKernelCreateInfo<ONNX_OPERATOR_KERNEL_CLASS_NAME(kAclExecutionProvider, kOnnxDomain, 6, Relu)>());
ret_val =
kernel_registry.Register(BuildKernelCreateInfo<ONNX_OPERATOR_VERSIONED_KERNEL_CLASS_NAME(kAclExecutionProvider, kOnnxDomain, 7, 9, Gemm)>());
In onnxruntime/core/providers/acl/acl_common.cc, fixed an unused-variable warning:

--- a/onnxruntime/core/providers/acl/acl_common.cc
+++ b/onnxruntime/core/providers/acl/acl_common.cc
@@ -70,7 +70,8 @@ void importDataFromTensor(arm_compute::Tensor* tensor, T* data){
// copy input tensor into the larger buffer
arm_compute::execute_window_loop(
aclInpuWindow,

 [&](const arm_compute::Coordinates& co) {
+// [&](const arm_compute::Coordinates& co) {

 [&](const arm_compute::Coordinates&) {
In onnxruntime/core/providers/acl/nn/conv.cc, fixed 'used uninitialized' error:

arm_compute::ActivationLayerInfo::ActivationFunction acl_activ_func;
arm_compute::ActivationLayerInfo::ActivationFunction acl_activ_func = arm_compute::ActivationLayerInfo::ActivationFunction::RELU;
‚Äã‚Äã

Compile onnxruntime:
dhunt@ubu-sw4:/dump/dump201/dhunt/onnxruntime$ make -j 6

That will run for 15 - 30 minutes.

Run it on DK
cp from onnxruntime to /sdcard/ACL

-rwxr-xr-x    1 root     users      1935834 Apr 12 01:13 libarm_compute.so
-rwxr-xr-x    1 root     users      6030808 Apr 12 01:13 libarm_compute_core.so
-rwxr-xr-x    1 root     users       818040 Apr 12 01:13 libarm_compute_graph.so
-rwxr-xr-x    1 root     users       721592 Apr 12 01:41 libcustom_op_library.so
-rwxr-xr-x    1 root     users    495493880 Apr 12 01:21 libonnxruntime.so.1.3.1
‚Äã‚Äã

onnxruntime_shared_lib_test

onnxruntime_api_tests_without_env

onnxruntime_global_thread_pools_test

onnxruntime_mlas_test

onnxruntime_perf_test

onnxruntime_test_all

/testdata

And put squeezenet1.0-9 into testdata/

‚Äã‚Äã

On DK:
cd /usr/lib
ln -s /sdcard/ACL/libarm_compute.so libarm_compute.so
ln -s /sdcard/ACL/libarm_compute_core.so libarm_compute_core.so
ln -s /sdcard/ACL/libarm_compute_graph.so libarm_compute_graph.so
ln -s /sdcard/ACL/libcustom_op_library.so libcustom_op_library.so
ln -s /sdcard/ACL/libonnxruntime.so.1.3.1 libonnxruntime.so
ln -s /sdcard/ACL/libonnxruntime.so.1.3.1 libonnxruntime.so.1.3.1
‚Äã‚Äã

Run any of the tests above.

Run the squeezenet model with ACL and without ACL:


# onnxruntime_perf_test -m times -r 10 -e acl /sdcard/testdata/squeezenet1.0-9/model.onnx result.csv
